snippet.textDisplay:
When kids are involved it will be tricky!

I’m not against prenups but what if they decide for one of them to be a stay at home parent for a few years or to homeschool?
What happens when one of them has to miss work when their children are sick, when they have appointments to take them to.
What if they were to get injured or ill?

Bills should also be split 50/50 but taking into account what I said above one of them might have more money than the other and be able to pay more into the expenses.

One of them is always going to give up more than the other to take care of the children and the household, and it will usually be the person who makes less money.

This is why in marriage you share everything and there is no ‘U’ or ‘I’. And why it is till death do us part.
